reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute small shoe rack
reviews.reviewText: This shoe rack is good for the price its just very small some sneakers do not fit because the boxes are small but its good for slippers. It was very easy to assemble and its very sturdy but i will be ordering a new shoe rack soon only because certain shoes cannot fit but if u have smaller feet or small kids this is perfect.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These were a great solution to the pile of shoe problem in my house. Very easy to assemble and the height and width were perfect to fit under the island in my kitchen. Only drawback is that they are not big enough to contain a pair of cowboy boots unless you scrunch the top of the boot. Wish that they had the capability to leave out two shelves instead of just one. Overall a good product. I ordered one more to balance out the space.

reviews.reviewerName: Emory L Morgan Jr.Emory L Morgan Jr.
reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Made only for tiny feet or kids’ shoes!!
reviews.reviewText: I was really hoping that this would be good enough for my winter boots after coming in from the outside, or at least a pair of sneakers on each level with one level for boots. Unfortunately, these definitely were not made, width wise, or height, wise, for Americanized shoes. I have size 12 feet and I can’t even get one shoe next to the other side-by-side. Not to mention if I do a single level, I have to squeeze them in there because the sneakers hit the top of the shelf on a single level. I ended up making two double levels, which will have to accommodate my shoes one in normally, and one on its side. If I end up keeping this, I will have to buy another set to go on top of that. I know they specify the size and I was really hoping this would fit my shoes better, but I underestimated the size. I guess it’s only made for Asian feet and children’s feet, measure carefully before buying! Other than that you get what you pay for, it’s a bit wobbly but sturdy enough for lightweight shoes. So this would be great in a kids closet or an entryway for little kids shoes up to maybe about a size 8. It doesn’t have any channels to let water drip onto so I may have to put a piece of terrycloth or microfiber on each level to absorb any wetness from the winter snow or rain. My advice, by American made it’s made for American feet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So far, so good
reviews.reviewText: This was purchased for a purpose other than shoes; it is used to store spare E-bike batteries.It is sturdy, and 2 batteries fit on each shelf. Due to the battery weight, we assembled & used only the base & one shelf above.It has only been one week. So far, so good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars I can't believe this thing was $60
reviews.reviewText: This shoe rack must be made for tiny shoes. There is no way it would fit my husband's size 12 shoes or boots. It was also a bit of a pain to put together and was not sturdy at all. I had to return it; it was not worth it for over $60. However, the worst part was trying to get all the pieces back into the box for the return. It was nearly impossible and I had to get a bigger box for it. Save your money!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Compact yes, but to compact for shoes to even fit!
reviews.reviewText: Negative comments first from daughter: This thing really is compact, but it's so much so you can't fit my shoes in without having to shove them in a bit. There is very little room above the shoesto let airflow in, and it's not deep enough and the shoes hang out more than I'd like (almost half the heel is out) so while is technically fits I guess it's way to tight. I wear a size 10wide in women's for reference. Everything needs another 1-2inches to breath. The shelves need to be 1-2 inches higher to keep the layers from covering the shoes. That much deeper so the shoe is fully in. That much wider so they aren't being scrapped and shoved against each other to fit.Pros: easy to put together, and you could easily buy more packs and keep building on or even go on the side a bit. I think a 6 tier would be perfect for me. The 4 fits great under my desk and I could potentially get a 5th tier on it and it may still fit so it's true it's very compact.This would be great for people with small shoes to hold lots of flip flops and slippers, or for KIDS. The limited space wouldn't be a major issue with slippers or cheap flimsy flip-flops that are easy to clean and tuck away. Kids shoes being smaller will fit well with this. A older kid or young teen whose growing their shoe tastes and collection would benefit from this. Easy to shove in a closet and keep organized.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for small places.
reviews.reviewText: Could be a little sturdier for heavier shoes like boots but great for an area that you do not want something large. Used mine by front door. Perfect so bought two. Two still did not take up a lot of space.
Not easy to find something to fit in my small space but this works perfectly. Easy to assemble.

Ho acquistato la scarpiera e sono rimasto soddisfatto del mio acquisto. Questo prodotto mi ha aiutato a mantenere il mio ingresso pulito e ordinato.La caratteristica che apprezzo di più di questa scarpiera è la sua impilabilità. Ogni paio di scarpe ha il suo spazio separato, il che rende più facile trovare quello che sto cercando e mantiene le scarpe in ordine.Un'altra caratteristica è l'altezza regolabile. Posso facilmente rimuovere il ripiano centrale della scarpiera per creare uno spazio più alto, perfetto per riporre stivali più lunghi o altri oggetti come borse o piante in vaso. Questa versatilità mi consente di utilizzare la scarpiera per scopi diversi e sfruttare al massimo lo spazio disponibile.L'installazione della scarpiera è stata semplice e veloce. Ci sono solo due tipi di pannelli di plastica come accessori e ho potuto completare il montaggio in pochi minuti.. Occupa poco spazio e si adatta facilmente a diversi ambienti.La stabilità di questa scarpiera è un altro punto a favore. Il design del pannello a forma di U e la partizione ispessita garantiscono una maggiore stabilità e capacità di carico. Non mi preoccupo di deformazioni anche quando metto scarpe più pesanti, grazie anche al bordo sollevato di ogni partizione che impedisce alle scarpe di scivolare.In conclusione, la scarpiera salvaspazio è un buon prodotto che consiglio . È versatile, funzionale, facile da montare e offre la soluzione ideale per mantenere le scarpe ordinate in diversi ambienti.
